Nesse vídeos apresentamos os conceitos básicos relacionados à Teoria das Probabilidades, incluindo a definição axiomática e conceitos de teoria dos conjuntos, probabilidade condicional, independência e a lei da probabilidade total. Diversos exemplos também são apresentados no vídeo.

Francisco A. Rodrigues is an associate professor at the Institute of Mathematics and Computer Science (ICMC), University of São Paulo. From February 2018 to February 2019, Francisco was a visiting professor at the University of Warwick, Mathematics Institute, working at the Centre for Complexity Science. He was awarded a Leverhulme Visiting Professorship. Francisco was also a visiting researcher at the Potsdam Institute for Climate Research, at the University of Zaragoza and at the Complexity Science Hub Vienna. Francisco was an invited lecturer at the Aschaffenburg University of Applied Sciences, Germany. His research includes complex systems, statistical physics of social dynamics, complex networks and machine learning. Francisco has authored more than 85 scientific articles in international journals, including Physical Review Letters, Advances in Physics, Physics Reports, Physical Review X, Climate Dynamics, among others. These papers have received more than 4,500 citations. He also authored the book "An Introduction to Multiplex Networks: Basic Formalism and Structural Properties", published by Springer in 2018. He concluded the supervision of nine master’s students, four PhDs and advised more than twenty undergraduate students. His teaching activities in graduate and undergraduate courses are related to the fields of Complex Systems, Network Science, Statistics, Mathematical Modelling, Stochastic Processes, Data Mining and Machine Learning. 

